<%= render partial: 'notices/shared/paragraph', :locals => {
  content: "Welcome to #{site_short_name}! This notice contains important information about renewing your health insurance coverage for your small business. Your renewal will be processed through #{site_short_name} this year. The #{site_short_name} team has been working closely with #{notice.plan_year.carrier_name} on your renewal, and #{notice.plan_year.carrier_name} has informed us that your policy is scheduled to be renewed on #{notice.plan_year.start_on}."} %>

<%= render partial: 'notices/shared/paragraph', :locals => {
  content: "<strong>If you want to keep your current coverage, we will renew you automatically in the coverage you are currently offering.</strong> You will begin receiving monthly invoices from #{site_short_name}, not your carrier."} %>

<%= render partial: 'notices/shared/paragraph', locals: {
  content: "<strong>If you work with a broker, your broker can do the renewal on your behalf.</strong> Brokers are able to manage your employee roster, make changes to your plan offerings prior to finalizing your plan offerings, and enroll employees once they have created an account on #{site_short_name}. If you would like to work with a broker and don’t have one, information about broker referrals is available on #{site_home_link.html_safe} under Get Help Find a Broker." } %>

<%= render partial: 'notices/shared/paragraph', :locals => {
  content: "<strong>#{site_short_name} offers 136 different plans from Aetna, CareFirst, Kaiser Permanente, and UnitedHealthcare</strong>. This includes high-deductible and zero deductible plans, PPOs, HMOs, and POS products.  Many small businesses that have purchased coverage through #{site_short_name} saved on premiums and were able to offer their employees a choice of plans. In fact, our current customers include the DC Chamber of Commerce, the Greater Washington Hispanic Chamber of Commerce, and the Restaurant Association Metropolitan Washington – all saved on premiums and improved coverage offered to their employees when they purchased through #{site_short_name}."} %>

<%= render partial: 'notices/shared/paragraph', :locals => {
  content: "#{site_short_name} makes offering choice to your employees easy for you. You can elect to offer all plans from a single carrier or plans from all carriers. You still would get only one bill even when your employees choose coverage from different carriers. Based on your budget you can select how much you contribute toward premiums and the level of coverage."} %>

<%= render partial: 'notices/shared/unordered_list', locals: {
  previous: "<strong>If you want to take a look at what #{site_short_name} has to offer small businesses, just go to #{site_home_link.html_safe} and create an account.</strong> Here is what you can do once you create an account:",
  listings: ["Review the health insurance plans you offer your employees and how much you contribute to their health insurance premiums. After you enter information about your business, you will be able to see your employees’ information as well as your plan offerings. If you do not see this information, your FEIN may be incorrect and you or your broker should contact us right away at (855) 532-5465 if this occurs.", "#{site_short_name} has the information for all of your employees enrolled in health insurance as of June 2016. If you have any new hires, recent terminations, or other employees who are eligible but not currently enrolled, work with your broker to include these changes to your employee roster prior to finalizing your plan offerings, so that these changes will reflect in your estimated monthly cost."] } %>

<%= render partial: 'notices/shared/paragraph', :locals => {
  content: "After working with your broker to update your employees’ information, you can review your plan offerings, your contribution to your employee’s premiums, and select a reference plan which will fix your costs. Your employees will also have until October 13, 2017 to make their plan selections."} %>

<%= render partial: 'notices/shared/paragraph', :locals => {
  content: "We are excited to serve your small business in meeting your health insurance needs.  If you have any further questions or need additional assistance, please do not hesitate to contact us at (855) 532-5465."} %>

<%= render partial: 'notices/shared/unordered_list', locals: {
  previous: "Please review the following attachments to this letter:",
  listings: ["Attachment 1 – When to go to your Carrier and to #{site_short_name}","Attachment 2 – Creating an Employer Account Walkthrough Guide"] } %>

<%= render partial: 'notices/shared/paragraph', :locals => { content: "Thank you,"} %>

<%= render partial: 'notices/shared/paragraph', :locals => { content: "#{site_short_name} Small Business Marketplace Team"} %>
